<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining form of
<xex>hydrogen</xex>, indicating <xex>hydrogen as an ingredient</xex>,
<as>as <ex>hydro</ex>chloric; or a <ex>reduction product obtained by
hydrogen</ex>, as <ex>hydro</ex>quinone.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

